OL,3,CMother and children died from exposure
OL,4,Cto fire in house blaze, inquest hears
OL,6,FMs Skerrett said a forensic
OL,7,Fpathologist had given a provisional
OL,8,Fcause of death for all three members
OL,9,Fof the Shearman family as "exposure to
OL,10,Fthe combustion products of fire,
OL,11,Fpending toxicology and microscopy".
OL,13,FThe court heard Mrs Shearman was
OL,14,Fformally identified from a tattoo on
OL,15,Fher body while her two children were
OL,16,Fidentified by DNA analysis.
OL,18,FThe coroner adjourned all three
OL,19,Finquests and did not set a further
OL,20,Fdate.
